  "time_ut": 1660984787,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2018\u2018\u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd6 \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc4\u0daf\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dbb\u0da2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"There is no help from the government to repair the houses burnt by the militants\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The members of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna have alleged that no support has been received from the government for the construction of the houses of the members of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna which were destroyed by the violent among the activists.",
        "They point out that Mr. Gotabhaya Rajapaksa had given some support for the construction of houses when he was the President, but no support has been received from the current government.",
        "It is reported that the construction of MP's houses is further delayed due to this reason",
        "Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe made a promise to the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna before he was appointed as the successor president that he would provide the necessary support to build the houses of the MPs destroyed by the violent.",
        "The MPs whose properties have been damaged have been given the opportunity to get houses on rental basis from the Battaramulla Viat Pura House Scheme and it is reported that only a few MPs have got the houses so far.",
        "A group of councilors said that it is very difficult to get those houses as there is a huge monthly premium.",
        "Meanwhile, it is reported that the family members of Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna's Polonnaru District Member of Parliament Mr. Amarakirthi Athukorala, who was killed by a group of violent people, have not received any assistance so far.",
        "Former minister Mr. Wimalaweera Dissanayake, who commented in this regard at the recently held government party meeting, has stated that since the family members of Mr. Amarakirthi Athukorala have not received any relief so far, he is requesting the President to take immediate action.",
        "On the 9th of May last May 9th, the property of the members of parliament and representatives of the local government bodies of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna was destroyed, including the houses of nearly one hundred people."
      ],
